# Make.com CMS Integration (Planned)

**Status:** Architecture agreed — do not implement until explicitly requested.
**Platform:** Make.com (not Zapier — Zapier free lacks webhooks + multi-step).

## Goal

Run qbuster-dashboard locally and in production **without deploying** `website-content-server` (Go server).

## Data store: website-content-server repo

GitHub: `babureddy-ui/website-content-server`

| File | Content |
|------|---------|
| `storage/industryPagesInd.json` | `{ "pages": [...] }` — type `industry` |
| `storage/outletPageInd.json` | `{ "pages": [...] }` — type `outlet` |
| `storage/users.json` | `{ "users": [...] }` — admin users |

## Architecture

```
Admin Panel (qbuster-dashboard)
  → /api/* routes (BFF layer, server-side only)
    → READ:  GitHub Contents API directly (Next.js)
    → WRITE: Make.com webhook → GitHub Contents API (read-modify-write + SHA)
```

Browser never calls Make or GitHub directly.

## Go server API contract (reference)

| Method | Endpoint | Make action |
|--------|----------|-------------|
| POST | `/api/login` | GitHub read `users.json` (no Make) |
| GET | `/api/users` | GitHub read (no Make) |
| POST | `/api/users` | `users.create` |
| DELETE | `/api/users/:id` | `users.delete` |
| GET | `/api/pages` | GitHub read (no Make) |
| GET | `/api/pages/:pageId` | GitHub read (no Make) |
| POST | `/api/createPage` | `pages.create` |
| PUT | `/api/pages/:pageId` | `pages.update` |

Response envelope: `{ "success": true, "message": "...", "data": ... }`

## Make.com scenario design

One scenario with Custom Webhook trigger + Router by `action`:

- `pages.create` — GET file → edit JSON → PUT with sha
- `pages.update` — find by pageId → replace → PUT
- `pages.delete` — remove by pageId → PUT
- `users.create` — append to users.json → PUT
- `users.delete` — remove by id → PUT

Filter step: reject if `secret` ≠ `WEBHOOK_SECRET`.

GitHub write token lives in Make connection only. Dashboard token is read-only.

## Webhook payload (dashboard → Make)

```json
{
  "action": "pages.create",
  "secret": "shared-secret",
  "payload": { }
}
```

## Env vars (dashboard — local + production)

```env
CONTENT_WEBHOOK_URL=https://hook.eu1.make.com/xxxxxxxx
WEBHOOK_SECRET=your-long-random-secret

GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_read_only_token
GITHUB_OWNER=babureddy-ui
GITHUB_REPO=website-content-server
GITHUB_BRANCH=main

AUTH_USERNAME=optional_dev_fallback
AUTH_PASSWORD=optional_dev_fallback
```

Remove `API_BASE_URL` — no Go server on port 8080.

## Make.com free tier limits

| Limit | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Operations/month | 1,000 |
| Active scenarios | 2 (use 1 scenario + router) |
| Ops per write | ~4–6 |
| Writes/month | ~200 |
| Writes/day (avg) | ~6–7 |

GET operations do not consume Make credits (handled via GitHub in Next.js).
Upgrade to Make Core (~$11/mo, 10k ops) if usage exceeds free tier.

## Dashboard file plan (when implemented)

- `app/lib/content-github.js` — GitHub reads (pages, users, login)
- `app/lib/webhooks.js` — `callContentWebhook(action, payload)`
- `app/api/content/pages.js` — full CRUD (GET direct, writes via Make)
- `app/api/content/users.js` — new
- `app/api/lib/auth.js` — constants only (`SESSION_COOKIE`, etc.)
- Remove `app/lib/backend.js` after migration

## Open decisions

1. Business validation in dashboard vs Make scenario
2. `pages.delete` — not in Go server today; add if admin UI needs it
3. Concurrent write handling (GitHub SHA conflicts — retry in Make)
4. Auth stays GitHub read of `users.json` (no Make for login)

## Implementation order

1. `content-github.js` + GET `/api/pages` from GitHub
2. Make scenario for `pages.create`
3. `webhooks.js` + POST `/api/pages`
4. Add update/delete + user actions in Make
5. Expand API routes + admin UI
6. Remove `backend.js` / `API_BASE_URL`
